This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with visual simultaneous localization and mapping (SLAM) algorithm. The paper also incorporates semantic segmentation and neural network uncertainty, which suggests that it could also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses a Bayesian neural network, which further supports its inclusion in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its method using the KITTI odometry dataset, which is commonly used in computer vision and robotics research, and is a popular benchmark for the computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CVPR) sub-category.
